        "username": "johscheuer",
        "avatar_template": "https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/j/f475e1/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2023-05-22T06:08:19.805Z",
        "cooked": "<p>What exactly do you mean with the <code>operand</code>? The operator needs the TLS setup to communicate with the FoundationDB cluster (if enabled) and the sidecars (if enabled).</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Wouldn\u2019t it should be ok if only RBAC is there for communication and control?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>If you mean Kubernetes RBAC, this is only used for access control for Kubernetes resources not for the sidecar or the FoundationDB cluster. Adopting RBAC would be more challenging and probably requires some additional tooling.</p>",
        "post_number": 4,
        "post_type": 1,
